---
import Layout from '@/components/chrome/Layout.astro';
import ClusterFunnelBlock from '@/components/chrome/ClusterFunnelBlock.astro';
import EmailCaptureCard from '@/components/funnel/EmailCaptureCard.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — strguests.tools"
  description="Why strguests.tools exists, what's free, what's paid, and how it connects to The STR Ledger."
  path="/about"
>
  <article class="bg-parchment">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-12 pb-9">
      <header>
        <p class="label text-[color:var(--accent-700)]">About</p>
        <h1 class="mt-3 text-h1 font-serif text-navy leading-tight">
          Free tools. No upsell<span class="period-gold">.</span>
        </h1>
      </header>

      <div class="prose mt-7 max-w-2xl">
        <h2>What this is</h2>
        <p>
          strguests.tools is a free toolkit for short-term rental hosts who want to delight guests
          without buying yet another piece of software. Branded printable PDFs (house rules, welcome
          books, Wi-Fi signs, check-in instructions) and 100+ Airbnb message templates for the
          conversations hosts have hundreds of times: booking confirmations, late-checkout requests,
          noise complaints, refund discussions.
        </p>

        <h2>What it isn't</h2>
        <p>
          It is not a SaaS. There is no subscription. There are no accounts. There is no AI summary
          of your business. Generation runs in your browser, your data stays on your device, and
          every PDF is yours forever.
        </p>

        <h2>Why we built it</h2>
        <p>
          We're the team behind <a href="https://thestrledger.com">The STR Ledger</a> — Excel
          workbooks and ops systems for Airbnb and VRBO hosts. After hosting our own properties for
          years, the gap was obvious: hosts spend hours each month writing the same five messages
          and printing the same four signs. The tools to fix that should be free, fast, and
          unintrusive.
        </p>
        <p>
          strguests.tools is funded by ads (eventually, after AdSense approval) and by hosts who
          discover us here and become STR Ledger customers. That funding model only works if the
          free tools are genuinely useful. So they are.
        </p>

        <h2>The cluster</h2>
        <p>
          strguests.tools is one of four free-tools sites we maintain for STR hosts at every stage
          of the lifecycle:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://strbuyers.tools">strbuyers.tools</a> — pre-purchase analysis</li>
          <li><a href="https://strhost.tools">strhost.tools</a> — math while running the property</li>
          <li><a href="https://strops.tools">strops.tools</a> — operations and turnover</li>
          <li>strguests.tools — guest XP (this site)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Privacy & data</h2>
        <p>
          Every PDF generator runs entirely client-side. Property addresses, photos, Wi-Fi
          passwords, and rules are processed in your browser; nothing is sent to a server.
          Email addresses you submit (lead magnet, newsletter) are stored only by our email
          service provider for the explicit purpose you opted into. We don't sell, share, or
          rent email lists.
        </p>

        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
        <p>
          Bug reports, tool requests, and partnerships welcome. <a href="/contact">Drop us a
          line</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <EmailCaptureCard magnet="strguests-newsletter" toolSlug="about" />
    </div>

    <ClusterFunnelBlock currentCluster="guest-xp" />
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose :global(h2) { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--t-h2-size); color: var(--brand-navy); margin-top: 1.6rem; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .prose :global(p) { margin-bottom: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--ink-2); }
  .prose :global(ul) { margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem; padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .prose :global(li) { margin-bottom: 0.35rem; color: var(--ink-2); line-height: 1.55; }
  .prose :global(a) { color: var(--accent-700); text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
